cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.IR 

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques to automatically understand videos recorded by wearable cameras. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an unsupervised strategy based on manifold learning, which falls under the category of unsupervised learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also deals with the challenges of changing light conditions and unrestricted locations, which could fall under the categories of cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper proposes an application case of hand-detection, which could fall under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
